2
1 (c) A violation of chapter LXVIIA of the Michigan penal code,
2 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.462a to 750.462h, that is punishable by
3 imprisonment for life.
4 (d) A violation of the Michigan anti-terrorism act, chapter
5 LXXXIII-A of the Michigan penal code, 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.543a to
6 750.543z, that is punishable by imprisonment for life.
7 (2) An indictment for a violation or attempted violation of
8 section 13, 462b, 462c, 462d, or 462e of the Michigan penal code,
9 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.13, 750.462b, 750.462c, 750.462d, and
10 750.462e, may be found and filed within 25 years after the offense
11 is committed. This subsection shall may be known as "Theresa
12 Flores's Law".
13 (3) An indictment for a violation or attempted violation of
14 section 136, 136a, 145c, 520e, or 520g of the Michigan penal code,
15 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.136, 750.136a, 750.145c, 750.520e, and
16 750.520g, may be found and filed as follows:
17 (a) Except as otherwise provided in subdivision (b), an
18 indictment may be found and filed within 10 years after the offense
19 is committed or by the alleged victim's twenty-first birthday,
20 whichever is later.
21 (b) If evidence of the offense is obtained and that evidence
22 contains DNA that is determined to be from an unidentified
23 individual, an indictment against that individual for the offense
24 may be found and filed at any time after the offense is committed.
25 However, after the individual is identified, the indictment may be
26 found and filed within 10 years after the individual is identified
27 or by the alleged victim's twenty-first birthday, whichever is
28 later.
29 (4) An indictment for a violation of section 520c or 520d of
ELF H00182'25 (H-1) tvowag

3
1 the Michigan penal code, 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.520c and 750.520d,
2 may be found and filed as follows:
3 (a) Except as otherwise provided in subdivision (b), an
4 indictment may be found and filed within 15 years after the offense
5 is committed or by the alleged victim's forty-second birthday,
6 whichever is later.
7 (b) If evidence of the offense is obtained and that evidence
8 contains DNA that is determined to be from an unidentified
9 individual, an indictment against that individual for the offense
10 may be found and filed at any time after the offense is committed.
11 However, after the individual is identified, the indictment may be
12 found and filed within 15 years after the individual is identified
13 or by the alleged victim's forty-second birthday, whichever is
14 later.
15 (5) An indictment for a violation of section 219g of the
16 Michigan penal code, 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.219g, may be found and
17 filed as follows:
18 (a) Except as otherwise provided in subdivision (b), an
19 indictment may be found and filed within 15 years after the
20 offense.
21 (b) If evidence of the offense is obtained and that evidence
22 contains DNA that is determined to be from an unidentified
23 individual, an indictment against that individual for the offense
24 may be found and filed at any time after the offense is committed.
25 However, after the individual is identified, the indictment may be
26 found and filed within 15 years after the individual is identified.
27 (6) (5) As used in subsections (3) and (4):to (5):
28 (a) "DNA" means human deoxyribonucleic acid.
29 (b) "Identified" means the individual's legal name is known
